cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper proposes a pruning scheme for reducing the size and computational complexity of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that is specifically designed for hardware implementation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of hardware accelerators, which could fall under the sub-categories of neural engineering (cs.NE) or architecture (cs.AR).
